column5: At least it's still warm and toasty in Ontario.
I like ice fishing.  -36, no thanks, you can have it
Go drill some holes already.  No ice here in Fergus.
I'll be iceishing in Ontario Monday or Tuesday at the latest.
-17 here tomorrow night, and a few cm's of snow tonight.  -36 is a little unreasonable.  No time for that crap.

I'll be iceishing in Ontario Monday or Tuesday at the latest.  I am definitely going to have a look!  Not sure how far I will need to drive though..  The spot I am eager to check has the next three nights at or close to minus double digits, and bellow zero all day.  It's worth strapping on the float suite and going for a poke!

Tried for a bit but the reel froze up lol,  just for those who don't know I don't fish in a hut, but yesterday I wish I had of , the east wind sucked, but it was friggin cold none the less, just a good reason to get some quick fresh air after the turkey dinner, better days ahead next week Dave, tropical minus 25 wc
Gonna be beauty next weekend. -7 and -5. I'll be on the road home though.
ha ha spring time fishing weather in January,,,,,pinch me lol, just checked long range, your absolutely right for next weekend, be fishing in a t shirt
You have a long drive ahead of you, or very wishful thinking.  S.
You have a long drive ahead of you, or very wishful thinking.  S.  Maybe he,s heading to Simon land.
I'll be out somewhere around here on the 31st.

Might as well put a zero on the end of-36, feels like -46C COMEON MAN!! I won't be braving -10 unless I have to leave the comforts of my place sometime in the future, last year anyway. No way, no how. But I'm told it's a dry cold!, Yea right. Like 101F is a dry heat in Arizona, it's too hot to breath.
Maybe, but thats one hell of a drive!! 20 hours.....
-36 is staring out the window sipping good rye kinda weather
Hey John  your message box doesn't work and I could use some fishing directions..I just may head up there the end of january

Yea right. Like 101F is a dry heat in Arizona, it's too hot to breath. One year in Vegas we did a bus tour to Laughlin for a day and it got up to 112F. As soon as you walked out of the Casino that wall of heat just hits you. Then  you walk around a bit and you realize your not even sweating. That dry heat is awesome. I would take 112F down there 7 days a week before I'd do 20 minutes outside in my veggie garden here in the summer with anything sunny and over 80F.
